## ✅ Checklist

**MUST verify before implementing this pattern:**

- [ ] List page hook reads URL params on mount
- [ ] List page hook syncs state when URL params change
- [ ] List page passes current state when navigating to detail
- [ ] Detail page reads query params from URL
- [ ] Detail page passes params back when returning to list
- [ ] List page is wrapped with Suspense
- [ ] Default values are provided for all params
- [ ] Numeric values are validated and parsed
- [ ] Empty params are not included in URL
- [ ] SSR compatibility is handled (window check)

---

## 🎓 Summary

**MUST ALWAYS** use this pattern for list-detail navigation flows. It ensures a **seamless user experience** by preserving search and pagination state across navigation. It follows **web standard practices** and provides benefits like:

- ✅ **Shareable URLs**: Users can bookmark or share filtered list views
- ✅ **Browser Navigation**: Back/forward buttons work correctly
- ✅ **State Persistence**: No data loss when navigating
- ✅ **Standard Practice**: Aligns with major web platforms

**Remember**: **MUST** use URL query parameters (not sessionStorage) for this pattern, and **MUST** ensure proper synchronization between URL and component state.
